*   The await keyword is used in an async function to ensure that all promises returned in the async function are synchronized,
    they wait for each other. Await eliminates the use of callbacks.

*   When we add some an other function inside of the callbacks it will be create a call back hell.Await eliminates the call back hell.

*   They can handle multiple asynchronous operations easily and provide better error handling than callbacks and events.

*   ES6 promises are faster and recommended than old callbacks.

*   I used axios library for call externale API. Becouse request has been deprecated and axios can easyly manage and  suported async    and  there are so many key features have inside of the package. We can get responces derectly as a Buffer.